      <h2>Hers</h2>
      <p>Before Samuel and I became friends, he was just "that nice guy who took my sisters out for fieldtrips with his niece." Oh, and I didn't know him as Samuel; his nickname was Slim. Go figure ;)</p>
      <p>Our friendship kicked off one day when I called to ask him about his car. I was planning to get a new one, and I really liked his. (How did we have each other's numbers, you may ask? He asked me for my number a few months earlier, though he'll never admit to that!) It was so easy to talk to him. We had so many similarities &mdash; music, passion for worship, love of food, babies, and so much more. But the more we talked, the more we realized there was something even deeper going on. We realized that God was doing something pretty amazing in our lives; the pieces were just lining up too perfectly!</p>
      <p>And now, here we are! Samuel is such a caring, thoughtful, patient, and God-fearing man. To top it off, he's super cute, funny, and athletic too! I love how he loves others and how he is a big brother to my sisters. Back when we started talking, I always thought this was too good to be true. And now, I still think that I'm too lucky and blessed to have him as my husband. I can't thank God enough for bringing Samuel into my life. I'm excited for our journey ahead!</p>
    </div>
  </div>
