      <h2>His</h2>
      <p>Mishal and I met at church and started becoming really good friends over the last few years. Before that, I would occasionally take my niece and Mishal's sisters on field trips, so Mishal and I have known each other for a lot longer.</p>
      <p>I knew there was something special about her as I began to know her more and more. Her maturity, both spiritually and intellectually, amazed me from the start. Growing up, I had a list of qualities I wanted in my future wife that I only told God and Sibi (best man) about. Mishal fulfilled all those and more! As our friendship grew, I slowly began to realize that she was the girl placed into my life for a specific reason. She continues to amaze me with her love for God and others.</p>
      <p>If I had to pick one of my favorite qualities (among many), it's her smile. It has to be a record of some kind! No one shows more teeth than she does when she smiles. I sometimes wish her face could be frozen in that positon. She has a passion for church, music, children, and sports (she likes watching; I like playing), which add to the incredible person she is. Eating is also something we love to do together, although it may not look like it. I am very grateful to know her and am excited to see what the future holds for our marriage.</p>
